  "title": "Assembly Technician (Semiconductor)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Perform sub-module assembly and in-house qualification of semiconductor equipment.</li>\n  <li>Set up machines to meet internal buy-off requirements and create setup instructions.</li>\n  <li>Develop checklists for module assembly and integration; identify extra parts for BOM updates.</li>\n  <li>Ensure modified part drawings are accurately updated and documented.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>NITEC in Mechanical/Electrical/Mechatronics Engineering or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>At least 1 year of hands-on experience in <strong>assembling and testing complex electrical and mechanical subassemblies</strong>, preferably in <strong>semiconductor manufacturing environments</strong>.</li>\n  <li>Skilled in using precision tools and understanding geometrical tolerance control.</li>\n  <li>Proficient in Microsoft Word, Excel, PowerPoint, and basic image editing tools.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in <strong>MS Word</strong> to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701</p>\n<p>Registration: R21100996</p>",
